<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><Regulation lims:pit-date="2006-03-22" lims:lastAmendedDate="2006-03-22" lims:current-date="2025-07-24" lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698550" lims:id="698550" regulation-type="SOR" xml:lang="en" xmlns:lims="http://justice.gc.ca/lims"><Identification lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698551" lims:id="698551"><InstrumentNumber>SOR/2002-422</InstrumentNumber><RegistrationDate><Date><YYYY>2002</YYYY><MM>11</MM><DD>21</DD></Date></RegistrationDate><ConsolidationDate lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22"><Date><YYYY>2025</YYYY><MM>7</MM><DD>25</DD></Date></ConsolidationDate><EnablingAuthority lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698553" lims:id="698553"><XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="E-5.401">EMPLOYMENT EQUITY ACT</XRefExternal></EnablingAuthority><LongTitle lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698554" lims:id="698554">Order Specifying the Royal Canadian Mounted Police for the Purposes of the Employment Equity Act</LongTitle><RegulationMakerOrder><RegulationMaker>P.C.</RegulationMaker><OrderNumber>2002-1958</OrderNumber><Date><YYYY>2002</YYYY><MM>11</MM><DD>21</DD></Date></RegulationMakerOrder></Identification><Order lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698555" lims:id="698555"><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698556" lims:id="698556" language-align="yes" format-ref="indent-0-0" list-item="no"><Text>Whereas, pursuant to paragraph 4(1)(d) of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="E-5.401">Employment Equity Act</XRefExternal><FootnoteRef idref="footnote1_e">a</FootnoteRef>, the Treasury Board has consulted the Solicitor General of Canada concerning the application of that Act to the Royal Canadian Mounted Police;</Text><Footnote id="footnote1_e" placement="page" status="official"><Label>a</Label><Text>S.C. 1995, c. 44</Text></Footnote></Provision><Provision lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698557" lims:id="698557" format-ref="indent-0-0" language-align="no" list-item="no"><Text>Therefore, Her Excellency the Governor General in Council, on the recommendation of the Minister of Labour and the Treasury Board, pursuant to paragraph 4(1)(d) of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="E-5.401">Employment Equity Act</XRefExternal><FootnoteRef idref="footnote1_e">a</FootnoteRef>, hereby makes the annexed <XRefExternal reference-type="act">Order Specifying the Royal Canadian Mounted Police for the Purposes of the Employment Equity Act</XRefExternal>.</Text></Provision></Order><Body lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698558" lims:id="698558"><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698559" lims:id="698559" level="1"><TitleText>Designation</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:lastAmendedDate="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698560" lims:id="698560"><Label>1</Label><Text>The Royal Canadian Mounted Police is specified under paragraph 4(1)(d) of the <XRefExternal reference-type="act" link="E-5.401">Employment Equity Act</XRefExternal> as a portion of the public sector employing one hundred or more employees to which that Act applies.</Text></Section><Heading lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698561" lims:id="698561" level="1"><TitleText>Coming into Force</TitleText></Heading><Section lims:inforce-start-date="2006-03-22" lims:lastAmendedDate="2006-03-22" lims:fid="698562" lims:id="698562" type="transitional"><Label>2</Label><Text>This Order comes into force on the day on which it is registered.</Text></Section></Body></Regulation>